window.docContents[247].resolve({"/Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry/Forthcoming-in-mathlib/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry--Forthcoming-in-mathlib--Newton-Polygons":{"contents":"Mathlib's Newton polygon of a polynomial (or power series)  over a\nvalued field () is the lower convex hull of the points  for\n. The slopes of its edges record the valuations of the roots: an edge of slope \nand horizontal length  corresponds to  roots of valuation .PR #38050 introduces the Newton-polygon API in mathlib itself — the same combinatorial object\ndeveloped for -adic power series in the NewtonPolys project ();\nonce merged it supplies the in-library foundation for ramification, factorisation of -adic\npolynomials, and slope decompositions of elliptic-curve formal groups.\nIn review — mathlib PR #38050.\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Elliptic Curves and Arithmetic Geometry\u0009Forthcoming in mathlib","header":"7.13.2. Newton Polygons","id":"/Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry/Forthcoming-in-mathlib/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry--Forthcoming-in-mathlib--Newton-Polygons"},"/Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry/The-Hasse-bound/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry--The-Hasse-bound--Point-Count-Over-Finite-Fields":{"contents":"For a Weierstrass curve  over a finite field  whose affine point type is\nfinite, the point count  is the cardinality of the finite abelian group\n () of -rational\nnonsingular affine points together with the point at infinity. In Hasse-Weil this is\npointCount E := Fintype.card E.Point.\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Elliptic Curves and Arithmetic Geometry\u0009The Hasse bound","header":"7.11.1. Point Count Over Finite Fields","id":"/Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry/The-Hasse-bound/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Elliptic-Curves-and-Arithmetic-Geometry--The-Hasse-bound--Point-Count-Over-Finite-Fields"}});